==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ordovician
<hw>Or`do*vi"cian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<etsep>Ordovices</etsep>, a Celtic people in Wales.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a division of the Silurian
formation, corresponding in general to the Lower Silurian of most
authors, exclusive of the Cambrian.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>The Ordovician formation.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ordure</ent>⟦br⟧
